{"type":"data","nodes":[{"type":"data","data":[{"debug":1},true],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"slug":1,"metadata":2,"images":99,"html":187,"xml":235},"ISic001830",{"file":1,"uri":1,"title":3,"status":4,"editions":6,"editionAuthor":17,"type":18,"support":22,"objectType":23,"material":27,"condition":34,"dimensions":35,"layoutDesc":46,"handNote":53,"date":67,"places":72,"geo":82,"country":77,"provenance":74,"provenanceFound":86,"provenanceGeo":94,"provenanceObserved":95,"provenanceLost":17,"graphics":99,"region":106,"settlement":79,"repository":107,"idno":122,"textLang":124,"bibliographyEdition":128,"bibliographyDiscussion":142,"citation":145,"tmNumber":34,"facsimile":166,"letterHeights":167,"publications":172,"zotero":174,"keywords":176,"lettering_types":186},"Building inscription of Martinianos",{"_":5},"draft",[7,9,11,13,15],{"type":8},"TM",{"type":10},"EDR",{"type":12},"EDH",{"type":14},"EDCS",{"type":16},"PHI",null,{"_":19,"ana":20,"ref":21},"building","#function.building","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/.html","9 fragments of a white marble plaque. The fragments consist of two joining sets, with an unquantifiable gap between them. Two fragments join to preserve part of the left margin; seven fragments join to preserve part of the upper and right margin, including the upper right corner; the lower margin is not preserved. The total width of the preserved fragments is 86cm, therefore the original total width was greater; the maximum preserved height is 35cm (so the total height was greater); thickness is 3 cm.",{"_":24,"ana":25,"ref":26},"plaque","#object.plaque","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259",{"_":28,"ana":29,"type":30,"subtype":31,"ref":33},"marble","#material.inorganic.stone","stone.unspecified",[32],"unverified","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html","",[36,40,43],{"_":37,"unit":38,"dimension":39},"35 (preserved minimum)","cm","height",{"_":41,"unit":38,"dimension":42},"86 (preserved minimum)","width",{"_":44,"unit":38,"dimension":45},"3","depth",{"layout":47},{"p":48,"rs":49,"damage":34},"Traces of three lines of ancient Greek are preserved, with guidelines above and below; upper, left and right margins are partially preserved. The text appears to maintain a consistent margin on the left, but not on the right.",{"_":50,"ana":51,"ref":52},"chiselled","#execution.chiselled","http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"lettering":54,"dimensions":55},"Tall, regular, narrow letters, v-cut, with small serifs on the termination of strokes. Small deep triangular interpuncts. Alpha has broken bar; epsilon tall, narrow, with equal short horizontals; theta and omicron are rhomboid; mu has vertical first and last, with the diagonals starting below the top and only desencing to the mid-point; nu is similar; rho has small curved, closed loop; sigma is lunate but rectilinear, with very short horizontals.",[56,63],{"type":57,"l":58,"from":59,"to":60,"h":61,"unit":62,"atLeast":61,"atMost":61},"letterHeight","Line 1-2","line1","line2","110","mm",{"type":64,"l":65,"from":59,"to":60,"h":66,"unit":62,"atLeast":66,"atMost":66},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","20",{"_":68,"notBefore":69,"notAfter":70,"evidence":71},"Dated by reference to Flavius Martinianos, consularis of Sicily between 352 and 358 CE (Soraci)",352,358,"prosopography",[73,78],{"_":74,"type":75,"ref":76,"region":77},"Agrigentum","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462086","Sicilia",{"_":79,"type":80,"ref":81,"region":77},"Agrigento","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/6541860",[83],[84,85],37.32084,13.58876,{"_":87,"type":88,"subtype":89,"when":90,"geo":91},"The principal fragment was found during excavation of a lime kiln in room d1 of casa IIC of the quartiere ellenistico romano of Agrigento; it was subsequently reconnected with fragments found in the same approximate location in the 1950s.","found","discovered","2013",[92,93],37.297649,13.591579,[92,93],{"_":96,"type":97,"subtype":98,"geo":17},"no","ob